Title: On the Uniqueness of the Newton-Wigner Position Operator
Authors: Dan Radu Grigore
Comments: 10 pages, PLAIN-TEX
Journal-ref: Int.J.Theor.Phys. 32 (1993) 555-564
\\
  It is shown that the quantum position operator of Newton and Wigner for
non-zero mass systems is uniquely determined if one imposes a quantum
''manifest covariance'' condition of the same type as the similar condition of
Currie, Jordan and Sudarshan in the the framework of the Hamiltonian formalism.
